# Frontend Environment Variables (.env.example)
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# IMPORTANT: This is a template file. Copy it to .env and fill in your values.
# DO NOT commit .env with actual values to version control!
#
# Copy command: cp .env.example .env
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# API CONFIGURATION (Required)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Backend API URL - Update based on your environment
#
# Development (local): http://localhost:5000/api
# Production (Render): https://your-backend.onrender.com/api
#
# IMPORTANT: 
# - Must include /api at the end
# - No trailing slash
# - Use http:// for local, https:// for production
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:5000/api

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# NOTES
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# Vite Environment Variables:
# - All variables must be prefixed with VITE_ to be exposed to the browser
# - Variables are replaced at BUILD TIME, not runtime
# - Do NOT store sensitive secrets here (they are visible in the browser)
#
# Security:
# ✅ This file (.env.example) can be committed to Git
# ❌ The actual .env file should NEVER be committed
# ✅ Only store non-sensitive configuration here
# ❌ Never store API keys, secrets, or passwords
#
# Setup Instructions:
# 1. Copy this file: cp .env.example .env
# 2. Update VITE_API_URL with your backend URL
# 3. Restart dev server after changes: npm run dev
#
# Deployment:
# - Vercel: Project Settings → Environment Variables
# - Netlify: Site Settings → Environment Variables
# - Set VITE_API_URL to your production backend URL
#
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
